- I (Sector): A pie-wedge shape, typically including a circular arc and two straight lines (radii) connecting the arc endpoints to the center.
- J (Triangle): 3-sided polygon. Closed path with exactly 3 vertices or straight segments.
- K (Ellipse): An oval or circle; usually created with an SVG 'A' (arc) command forming a closed continuous curve that is not a polygon.
- If a circle is an option, it will have a label distinct from K (Ellipse). If only ellipse is available, select K for circular or elliptical closed arcs.

CLASSIFICATION PROCESS:
- Only base your answer on the SVG path commands and the resulting geometric structure. Do not consider text outside the path structure itself.
