- F: octagon (8-sided polygon)
- G: pentagon (5-sided polygon)
- I: sector (a “pie slice” or circular sector—bounded by a circular arc and two straight lines or radii meeting at a common point)
- J: triangle (3-sided polygon)
- K: ellipse (an oval shape—closed curve, all points sum of distances to two foci is constant. Use for perfect circles if only 'ellipse' is available)

**You must NOT infer or invent any categories that are not explicitly listed, even if other category words appear in the text or options.**

